HEADWORD: Physeter
<hw>Phy*se"ter</hw> <pr>(f⟦imac⟧*s⟦emac⟧"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>fyshth`r</grk>, fr. <grk>fysa^n</grk> to blow:
cf. F. <ets>phys⟦eacute⟧t⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety>
<mark>[capitalized]</mark> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The genus
that includes the sperm whale (<spn>Physeter
macrocephalus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A filtering machine operated by air
pressure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

